title: Arsenal and Tottenham in hot pursuit of teenage prodigy Tielemans
text:
Arsenal and Tottenham in hot pursuit of teenage prodigy Tielemans Teenage sensation Youri Tielemans starred in Anderlecht's win over Oostende (Getty Images) Arsenal have joined north London rivals Tottenham Hotspur in the hot pursuit of 19-year-old Anderlecht sensation Youri Tielemans, who starred on Monday (AEDT) for the Belgium outfit. Source: 
Tielemans has been widely touted as a future star and has already made an impressive 168 appearances for Anderlecht, having also debuted for Belgium in November 2016. Anderlecht prodigy Tielemans signs new deal Youri Tielemans has ended speculation over his future by signing a new five-year contract with Anderlecht. 
And now the teenage sensation, who plays in the Belgian Pro League along with Socceroos goalkeeper Mat Ryan's Genk, is being chased by Arsenal - joining an array of major European clubs showing interest in him, including Tottenham, according to Calciomercato . Ryan wanted to stay in Spain, but moved for game-time Australia shot stopper Mat Ryan hopes his loan move to Belgian club Genk will provide the game time he craves after long stints on the sideline during his time at Valencia. 
The interest is no surprise, particularly after the 19-year-old scored two incredible goals, in almost as many minutes, during Anderlecht's 4-1 win over Oostende in the Belgian Pro League . Youri Tielemans (19) for Anderlecht this season:
